European Stock Futures Rise as Investors Weigh Possible Fed Growth Support

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-08-25T06:14:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/european-stock-index-futures-climb-euro-stoxx-50-contract-increases-0-7-.html
(Corrects headline to show trading is in Euro Stoxx 50
futures.)  European stock-index futures
climbed, indicating the Stoxx Europe 600 Index may rise for a
fourth day, as investors continued to weigh whether Federal
Reserve policymakers meeting tomorrow will take action to help
the economy. Asian stocks rose and U.S. index futures slipped.  Futures on the Euro Stoxx 50 Index, a benchmark for the
euro area, climbed 0.7 percent to 2,250 at 7:08 a.m. in  London .
